description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Recovery Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Riverside Clinic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £36000-£40000&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthshare is a successful provider of clinical and diagnostic services to the NHS and private sectors across various locations throughout the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Riverside Clinic we have a 8 bedded day surgery unit and theatre complex with 1 theatre and 4 recovery bays. We will be providing day surgery which will include General, Orthopaedic, Gynaecology, Urology, ENT, Plastics. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced recovery practitioners to work in this environment. The post holder will ensure that professional and national standards are practiced in the Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Theatre Recovery Practitioner, you will be responsible for the total nursing care of individual patients within the recovery area and ensure recovery criteria is adhered to before discharging patients. In addition to this, you will also actively contribute to the maintenance of an environment that is conducive to the delivery and promotion of a high standard of patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver a consistently high standard of patient care utilising evidence based practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing, planning, delivering and evaluation of post-operative patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare the recovery in readiness to admit patients after surgical procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all equipment is checked prior to use and any faults reported to the Theatre Lead immediately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare patients and provide assistance for clinical/operative procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If interested apply now!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
